It’s been the hardest week for me. On Sunday, my milk completely dried up. I got nothing for days. I didn’t even try to get it back at first because this is the 3rd time that stress has caused my supply to tank, and i was extremely defeated. I was in pain, crying, and just overall so sad that my breastfeeding journey was going to end prematurely. 

I really woke up the other day and said “let me just give it one more try” so I started using @momcozy @momcozyofficial hands free massagers and the kneading massager + power pumping and trying to feed. I’m finally starting to get some milk back. I’m still giving Mav bottles from my freezer stash and mixing with half formula, but we’re making progress! 

It’s really easy to give up on hard things, but the reward from putting in effort and staying disciplined will always pay off. I’m really thankful I chose to not end my breastfeeding journey. It’s the hardest thing I’ve ever done in my life 😭

7 months postpartum & in the best shape of my life 🔥 How I did it👇 

• 80/20 nutrition. Meal prepping weekly, but still enjoying a drink 🥃 and desserts when I want. No special diet. I don’t track, I just eat a lot of lean protein. 
• prioritized core recovery (check my core restore program- completed this twice)
• weight training minimum 3x/week (even from home. I just do what I can) 
• walks 2x a day 
• water + @ehplabs oxyshred on empty stomach in the morning or before my workout (check the non-stim for my BF mamas) use code CAIT 

Everyone’s timeline is different. Real results take time. I am not lucky to have “snapped back”, I put a lot of time and work in. It’s never easy, I struggled with postpartum anxiety & depression but I did not allow my temporary mental state to sink me into a deeper hole. Choose to be your best self and trust the process…. Most importantly show up for yourself! 

If you don’t know where to start, join my online coaching team. I’ll help you through the process. Just be ready to show up 💙⭐️ DM me or visit the link on my page. 

#postpartumbody #postpartumfitness #postpartumjourney #fitmom #bodytransformation #mombod #fitnessmotivation #fitnessjourney

5’9 , 175lb, 7 months postpartum. Current goal: glute growth, athletic performance 🤸‍♀️ 

What’s yours? ⬇️

The two tips that have gotten me the most results on my fitness journey: 

1. Make everything a core exercise 
- why is this important? ➡️ weightlifting is the best core workout you could do. Engaging your core or “bracing” allows for a safer, more effective lift. It’s going to prevent injuries while strengthening your core muscles. Sit ups are not getting you stronger… give yourself this cue and watch your strength and aesthetics improve like crazy. 

2. Training to failure vs reps 
- this is situational but training to failure regularly is a big driving factor to results I have gotten as well as my clients. This allows you to tap into your full potential in the gym. It’s going to help increase your muscle strength and size- and paired with proper nutrition you got yourself a recipe for success! You gonna be strong and lean! I recommend finding a range to stay between… for example for squats I’ll do 4 working sets as heavy as I can, for 3-6 reps. I do what I can with the heaviest weight I can. 

For a structured program, check out my online coaching 🫶🏼

Maverick’s dinner for the next couple days: Cod + Sambiot with steamed broccoli 

Recipe ⬇️ 

Cod: 
• cut into portion sizes 
• season with oil, pepper, paprika, lemon juice 
• cook in a pan for 3-4 min each side or until fully cooked 

Sambiot: 
• add day old rice to small pot 
• cover rice fully with chicken broth 
• add in finely chopped carrots, a small chunk of ginger and 2 cloves garlic 
• bring to a boil and add a little chick bouillon, stir 
• turn to low and cover 
• simmer until rice is mushy and carrots are soft 
• remove garlic and ginger chunk 

This is one of Mav’s favorite things to eat. I love being able to feed him things I ate as a child! Slowly introducing new proteins to him as he gets older- the cod was definitely a hit! This is super easy to make ahead for 2-3 days at a time and very healthy for baby!

My recent obsession- nutrient dense grain bowl that yields a ton of protein and checks off every nutritional box for me! This is great for lunch meal prep, and you can eat hot or cold! Next time I’m adding a boiled egg for even more protein. Recipe ⬇️

Asian glaze chicken 👅 my portion yields ~35g protein! 

Recipe: 
• wash rice and cook with kettle and fire broth (any kind is fine- but this container holds 19g protein!!!) 
• coat cubed chicken thighs in cornstarch and salt, pepper, garlic, onion, ground ginger 
• set aside to make sauce 
• sauce: soy, sweet soy, rice vinegar, sesame oil, honey (I use mikes hot honey for a kick) , minced garlic - fresh only 
•heat neutral oil in pan
• sauté chicken and add sauce once 90% complete 
• let sauce thicken then set chicken aside (leave all the sauce residue in pan)
• add a little more oil and garlic to hot pan and cook kale until wilted 
• add a little oyster  sauce once kale is almost done cooking 
•plate and enjoy!

PS- I measure nothing, ever 🙂 season to heart!!!

Normalize normal bodies ❤️ 

10 month postpartum first time mom here 👋🏽 My body has become extremely sensitive since giving birth, and I’ve noticed it easily fluctuates. However, I feel very in tune with my body and stepping into the new year one of my goals is to cycle sync my workouts and nutrition. 

If you haven’t heard of cycle syncing, it’s basically lining up your activity and eating depending upon which stage of your menstrual cycle you’re in. I’ll be talking more in depth about this on my fitness page @caitfitapp 

Even when my body isn’t where I’d like it to be, I’m happy with what I see in the mirror. There is always room to grow and we are our harshest critics! The world can be cruel, so be the positive and encouraging voice for yourself and remember body fluctuation is apart of being human.

My love language is cooking for Mav ❤️ this is a great idea for Saturday morning breakfast for your little one (or yourself 😝) recipe below ⤵️ 

1. Mash 1 small banana and 3 cut up strawberries 
2. Add 1 egg, 1/4 cup milk of choice, brown sugar, cinnamon and mix all together 
3. Cut off edges of bread for baby 
4. Heat butter over medium heat 
5. Coat all sides of bread and cook until done 
6. Slice into strips or cut into bite size pieces for baby! 

Served Mav’s with Cheerios because that’s his FAVORITE right now! Comment below if you make this and let me know what you think.

The wings y’all keep seeing on my IG story! Obsession recently. 

Recipe: 
1. Completely dry wings 
2. Season with salt, pepper, garlic, onion, sazon, lemon pepper, paprika + neutral oil 
3. Add baking powder & coat chicken fully 
4. Preheat airfryer to 400
5. Cook at 400 for 10 min 
6. Flip then cook for another 8-10 min 
7. While second side is frying- melt butter, honey, hot sauce, lemon pepper seasoning, and a little soy sauce in a pan 
8. Combine wings and sauce and enjoy!
